  <data name="swagger_remarks_webhookclient_callback" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>

        Description:
            Processes the result of executing an exit interface.
			
			This API is consumed by the WMS to notify subscribed client applications of the occurrence of exit interfaces.
            All exit interfaces are notified through the same endpoint.
            It is through one of the attributes of the incoming parameter ("id") that it is possible to determine the type of reported output.
            When consuming this API, the WMS includes an "X-Hub-Signature" HTTP header that contains the JSON hash of the incoming parameter 
			calculated from the "HMACSHA512" algorithm and the secret shared with the client application that makes this API available.
            The specific implementation of this API may use the aforementioned header to verify the authenticity of the received message.
            To do this, you must recalculate the hash of the incoming JSON, applying the same algorithm and secret shared 
			with the WMS and verify that it matches the one received through the HTTP header.
            In the WMS, this secret is configured at the company level from the Companies Panel and cannot exceed 50 characters.
			
            Decimals must be sent with '.'. The accepted date formats are: [yyyy-MM-dd], [yyyy/MM/dd], [MM/dd/yyyy] and [MM-dd-yyyy]</value>
  </data>
